text: Jennifer Carroll MacNeill ( Carroll; born 5 September 1980) is an Irish Fine Gael politician and lawyer. She has been the Minister of State for European Affairs since 2024. She was Minister of State at the Department of Finance from 2022 to 2024. She has been a Teachta Dála (TD) for the Dún Laoghaire constituency since the 2020 general election. ==References== Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Dublin Category:Irish lawyers
